natural problem: In an orchestra, $60\%$ of the musicians play string instruments, and the remainder play woodwind, brass, or percussion instruments. If the orchestra has 130 members, how many musicians do not play string instruments?
natural solution: We know a person can either play a string instrument or not play a string instrument. $60\% \times 130 = 78$ musicians play string instruments, yielding $130-78 = \boxed{52}$ musicians who do not play string instruments.

assumes h0 : "total_members = 130"

shows  "non_string_members = 52"
